339
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:55,200
Wh-What do you mean?

340
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,300
Can I take this back for now?

341
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:03,200
Here's the thing.

342
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:05,200
I wonder if you are interested

343
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:08,000
in sports economics and management.

344
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,400
You mean...

345
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:11,600
Our company cooperates

346
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:14,600
with top professional sports management teams in the country.

347
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:16,100
Not only can they help athletes

348
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:18,800
arrange training and competitions,

349
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:21,600
they also arrange commercial ads and endorsements.

350
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:24,700
What do you mean?

351
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:28,400
I heard you have great grades.

352
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:30,700
You can view our team's information first.

353
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:31,600
Take a look.

354
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,500
They are very capable.

355
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:36,100
They currently have almost 100 athletes under their management.

356
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:37,800
- Many are the...
- Wait a moment.

357
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:40,200
Isn't this an interview?

358
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,800
Yes, we are doing an interview.

359
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:44,000
Don't be nervous.

360
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:47,200
Let's just chat as friends.

361
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,700
Right now, you're young,

362
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,800
and you're in your prime.

363
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:55,300
But the golden age for track and field athletes is too short.

364
00:22:55,300 --> 00:22:57,200
You don't have to sign with us right now.

365
00:22:57,200 --> 00:23:00,600
Let our team arrange several events and endorsements for you,

366
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,000
then you can check out their abilities first.

367
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:02,800
Listen to me.

368
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,600
This is what I think.

369
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:09,200
I haven't really thought about that yet.

370
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:11,100
I'm going to go eat.

371
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:12,000
Let's talk about it next time.

372
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,000
But...

373
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:13,800
"Eat"?

374
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,400
What time is it? Will you eat already?

375
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:17,500
I get hungry very fast.

376
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:19,200
Then think about it carefully when you're eating.

377
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,100
Okay. Thank you.

378
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:26,300
Coach. Let's go.

379
00:23:26,300 --> 00:23:27,800
- Already done?
- The interview is over.

380
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:29,100
Let's go.

381
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:35,000
It's done.

382
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,800
I can't believe it.

383
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:42,500
Did you get hungry during an interview?

384
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:45,400
I'll tell you more about it later.

385
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:46,400
What were you watching?

386
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:48,600
You were laughing like a fool.

387
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,400
Look.

388
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,900
A video of you from Nationals.

389
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,700
Don't watch it.

390
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:58,800
Why are you so dumb?

391
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:00,000
What?

392
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,500
You know I'm ticklish yet you still tickle me.

393
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:03,000
Don't mess with me.

394
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,600
What if I do?

395
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:05,500
I'm warning you, don't mess with me.

396
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:06,400
So what if I do?

397
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,200
If you do it one more time...

398
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:09,400
If you do it one more time...

399
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:11,000
I was wrong.

400
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:12,600
- Were you wrong?
- I was wrong.

401
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:13,700
- Were you?
- Yes.

402
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:15,300
Now you know you were wrong;

403
00:24:15,300 --> 00:24:17,200
why didn't you realize when you were tickling me?

404
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:19,300
I tickled you, so what?

405
00:24:19,300 --> 00:24:20,300
Still being stubborn, right?

406
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:21,400
I am.

407
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,000
Can't I control you?

408
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,600
You can't.

409
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,800
So that's what happened.

410
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:50,200
No wonder you got an interview

411
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:52,400
without having any good results.

412
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,700
So they want you to have an agent.

413
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:59,000
Sports agencies are common overseas.

414
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,600
But here...

415
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,600
We begin to see more, though.

416
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,300
What do you think?

417
00:25:06,100 --> 00:25:07,600
I think not.

418
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:09,500
Training is more important.

419
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:12,200
Then turn her down.

420
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,600
Be nice to her.

421
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,500
Don't make things awkward.

422
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:19,500
This is the guy from the video, right?

423
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:20,600
Duan Yu Cheng?

424
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:22,200
He looks even more handsome in person.

425
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:24,400
He makes me want to become an athlete, too.

426
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:26,000
Don't even think about it.

427
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:28,000
I didn't know our university had such a handsome guy.

428
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:30,000
You're so likeable.

429
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:33,000
Everyone who watched the video confessed to you.

430
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:40,800
Then will you mind if they like me?

431
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,700
No.

432
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:45,700
Wouldn't it be worse if they hate you?

433
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:47,900
What if they like me in a romantic way?

434
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:51,100
What if

435
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:54,000
I become really famous, really rich,

436
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,500
then I become a bad boy and don't want you anymore?

437
00:25:55,500 --> 00:25:57,000
What would you do?

438
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:58,400
You won't.

439
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:01,100
How so?

440
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:02,800
There is no way.

441
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:05,200
You're not that kind of person.

442
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,300
How do you know I'm not that kind of person?

443
00:26:07,300 --> 00:26:09,200
I just know.

444
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,800
If you were,

445
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,800
I wouldn't fall for you.

446
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:20,200
Let's get married.

447
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,100
I'm serious.

448
00:26:24,300 --> 00:26:27,000
When I was in Jiangzhou last time, my dad told me to be responsible for you.

449
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,800
You are already their verified daughter-in-law.

450
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:30,700
If I don't marry you,

451
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:34,000
they will break my leg, seriously.

452
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:35,200
I'm leaving soon.

453
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:37,300
Just say yes. Okay?

454
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:39,300
Seriously, say yes.

455
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:45,500
How old-school is your family?

456
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:48,500
Before leaving home, must you get married?

457
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:50,000
Wait.

458
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,700
Did you say no

459
00:26:51,700 --> 00:26:53,900
because my proposal wasn't formal enough?

460
00:26:53,900 --> 00:26:55,500
I know it wasn't formal enough.

461
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:57,000
Then let's get engaged.

462
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,500
Getting engaged is okay, right?

463
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:00,300
You can say yes to getting engaged, right?

464
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:03,000
You will report to the national team in two days.

465
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:04,800
What nonsense are you thinking about

466
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:07,200
instead of considering the Asia Championships?

467
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:09,300
Get... getting married.

468
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:13,800
You have three seconds.

469
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:15,600
Sign it.

470
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:18,900
I said,
[Jump]

471
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:23,500
